g1301.definition: [διατηρέω] from {{g1223}} and {{g5083}}; to watch thoroughly, i.e. (positively and transitively) to observe strictly, or (negatively and reflexively) to avoid wholly

g1302.definition: [διατί] from {{g1223}} and {{g5101}}; through what cause ?, i.e. why?

g1303.definition: [διατίθεμαι] middle voice from {{g1223}} and {{g5087}}; to put apart, i.e. (figuratively) dispose (by assignment, compact, or bequest)

g1304.definition: [διατρίβω] from {{g1223}} and the base of {{g5147}}; to wear through (time), i.e. remain

g1305.definition: [διατροφή] from a compound of {{g1223}} and {{g5142}}; nourishment

g1306.definition: [διαυγάζω] from {{g1223}} and {{g826}}; to glimmer through, i.e. break (as day)

g1308.definition: [διαφέρω] from {{g1223}} and {{g5342}}; to bear through, i.e. (literally) transport; usually to bear apart, i.e. (objectively) to toss about (figuratively, report); subjectively, to "differ", or (by implication) surpass

g1309.definition: [διαφεύγω] from {{g1223}} and {{g5343}}; to flee through, i.e. escape

g1310.definition: [διαφημίζω] from {{g1223}} and a derivative of {{g5345}}; to report thoroughly, i.e. divulgate

g1311.definition: [διαφθείρω] from {{g1225}} and {{g5351}}; to rot thoroughly, i.e. (by implication) to ruin (passively, decay utterly, figuratively, pervert)

g1314.definition: [διαφυλάσσω] from {{g1223}} and {{g5442}}; to guard thoroughly, i.e. protect

g1315.definition: [διαχειρίζομαι] from {{g1223}} and a derivative of {{g5495}}; to handle thoroughly, i.e. lay violent hands upon

g1316.definition: [διαχωρίζομαι] from {{g1223}} and the middle voice of {{g5563}}; to remove (oneself) wholly, i.e. retire

g1318.definition: [διδακτός] from {{g1321}}; (subjectively) instructed, or (objectively) communicated by teaching

g1319.definition: [διδασκαλία] from {{g1320}}; instruction (the function or the information)

g1320.definition: [διδάσκαλος] from {{g1321}}; an instructor (genitive case or specially)

g1321.definition: [διδάσκω] a prolonged (causative) form of a primary verb δάω (to learn); to teach (in the same broad application)

g1322.definition: [διδαχή] from {{g1321}}; instruction (the act or the matter)

g1324.definition: [Δίδυμος] prolongation from {{g1364}}; double, i.e. twin; Didymus, a Christian

g1325.definition: [δίδωμι] a prolonged form of a primary verb (which is used as an alternative in most of the tenses); to give (used in a very wide application, properly, or by implication, literally or figuratively; greatly modified by the connection)

g1326.definition: [διεγείρω] from {{g1223}} and {{g1453}}; to wake fully; i.e. arouse (literally or figuratively)

g1327.definition: [διέξοδος] from {{g1223}} and {{g1841}}; an outlet through, i.e. probably an open square (from which roads diverge)

g1329.definition: [διερμηνεύω] from {{g1223}} and {{g2059}}; to explain thoroughly, by implication, to translate

g1331.definition: [διερωτάω] from {{g1223}} and {{g2065}}; to question throughout, i.e. ascertain by interrogation

g1332.definition: [διετής] from {{g1364}} and {{g2094}}; of two years (in age)

g1333.definition: [διετία] from {{g1332}}; a space of two years (biennium)

g1336.definition: [διηνεκής] neuter of a compound of {{g1223}} and a derivative of an alternate of {{g5342}}; carried through, i.e. (adverbially with {{g1519}} and {{g3588}} prefixed) perpetually

g1337.definition: [διθάλασσος] from {{g1364}} and {{g2281}}; having two seas, i.e. a sound with a double outlet

g1338.definition: [διϊκνέομαι] from {{g1223}} and the base of {{g2425}}; to reach through, i.e. penetrate

g1339.definition: [διΐστημι] from {{g1223}} and {{g2476}}; to stand apart, i.e. (reflexively) to remove, intervene

g1340.definition: [διϊσχυρίζομαι] from {{g1223}} and a derivative of {{g2478}}; to stout it through, i.e. asservate

g1342.definition: [δίκαιος] from {{g1349}}; equitable (in character or act); by implication, innocent, holy (absolutely or relatively)

g1343.definition: [δικαιοσύνη] from {{g1342}}; equity (of character or act); specially (Christian) justification

g1344.definition: [δικαιόω] from {{g1342}}; to render (i.e. show or regard as) just or innocent

g1345.definition: [δικαίωμα] from {{g1344}}; an equitable deed; by implication, a statute or decision

g1348.definition: [δικαστής] from a derivative of {{g1349}}; a judger

g1349.definition: [δίκη] probably from {{g1166}}; right (as self-evident), i.e. justice (the principle, a decision, or its execution)

g1350.definition: [δίκτυον] probably from a primary verb δίκω (to cast); a seine (for fishing)

g1351.definition: [δίλογος] from {{g1364}} and {{g3056}}; equivocal, i.e. telling a different story

g1352.definition: [διό] from {{g1223}} and {{g3739}}; through which thing, i.e. consequently

g1354.definition: [Διονύσιος] from Διόνυσος (Bacchus); reveller; Dionysius, an Athenian

g1355.definition: [διόπερ] from {{g1352}} and {{g4007}}; on which very account

g1356.definition: [διοπετής] from the alternate of {{g2203}} and the alternate of {{g4098}}; sky-fallen (i.e. an aerolite)

g1357.definition: [διόρθωσις] from a compound of {{g1223}} and a derivative of {{g3717}}, meaning to straighten thoroughly; rectification, i.e. (specially) the Messianic restauration

g1359.definition: [Διόσκουροι] from the alternate of {{g2203}} and a form of the base of {{g2877}}; sons of Jupiter, i.e. the twins Dioscuri

g1360.definition: [διότι] from {{g1223}} and {{g3754}}; on the very account that, or inasmuch as

g1361.definition: [Διοτρεφής] from the alternate of {{g2203}} and {{g5142}}; Jove-nourished; Diotrephes, an opponent of Christianity

g1362.definition: [διπλοῦς] from {{g1364}} and (probably) the base of {{g4119}}; two-fold

g1365.definition: [διστάζω] from {{g1364}}; properly, to duplicate, i.e. (mentally) to waver (in opinion)

g1368.definition: [διϋλίζω] from {{g1223}} and ὑλίζω (to filter); to strain out

g1369.definition: [διχάζω] from a derivative of {{g1364}}; to make apart, i.e. sunder (figuratively, alienate)

g1370.definition: [διχοστασία] from a derivative of {{g1364}} and {{g4714}}; disunion, i.e. (figuratively) dissension

g1371.definition: [διχοτομέω] from a compound of a derivative of {{g1364}} and a derivative of τέμνω (to cut); to bisect, i.e. (by extension) to flog severely

g1372.definition: [διψάω] from a variation of {{g1373}}; to thirst for (literally or figuratively)

g1374.definition: [δίψυχος] from {{g1364}} and {{g5590}}; two-spirited, i.e. vacillating (in opinion or purpose)

g1377.definition: [διώκω] a prolonged (and causative) form of a primary verb δίω (to flee; compare the base of {{g1169}} and {{g1249}}); to pursue (literally or figuratively); by implication, to persecute

g1378.definition: [δόγμα] from the base of {{g1380}}; a law (civil, ceremonial or ecclesiastical)

g1379.definition: [δογματίζω] from {{g1378}}; to prescribe by statute, i.e. (reflexively) to submit to, ceremonially rule

g1380.definition: [δοκέω] a prolonged form of a primary verb, δόκω (used only in an alternate in certain tenses; compare the base of {{g1166}}) of the same meaning; to think; by implication, to seem (truthfully or uncertainly)

g1381.definition: [δοκιμάζω] from {{g1384}}; to test (literally or figuratively); by implication, to approve

g1382.definition: [δοκιμή] from the same as {{g1384}}; test (abstractly or concretely); by implication, trustiness

g1383.definition: [δοκίμιον] neuter of a presumed derivative of {{g1382}}; a testing; by implication, trustworthiness

g1384.definition: [δόκιμος] from {{g1380}}; properly, acceptable (current after assayal), i.e. approved

g1385.definition: [δοκός] from {{g1209}} (through the idea of holding up); a stick of timber

g1388.definition: [δόλος] from an obsolete primary verb, δέλλω (probably meaning to decoy; compare {{g1185}}); a trick (bait), i.e. (figuratively) wile

g1390.definition: [δόμα] from the base of {{g1325}}; a present

g1391.definition: [δόξα] from the base of {{g1380}}; glory (as very apparent), in a wide application (literal or figurative, objective or subjective)

g1392.definition: [δοξάζω] from {{g1391}}; to render (or esteem) glorious (in a wide application)

g1394.definition: [δόσις] from the base of {{g1325}}; a giving; by implication, (concretely) a gift

g1395.definition: [δότης] from the base of {{g1325}}; a giver

g1396.definition: [δουλαγωγέω] from a presumed compound of {{g1401}} and {{g71}}; to be a slave-driver, i.e. to enslave (figuratively, subdue)

g1398.definition: [δουλεύω] from {{g1401}}; to be a slave to (literal or figurative, involuntary or voluntary)

g1399.definition: [δούλη] feminine of {{g1401}}; a female slave (involuntarily or voluntarily)
